e and priceless treasure; fit for all the kings through the  ages.  A trap door is embedded in the cavern's ceiling.#Recessed Entrance.#You are at a recessed section of the wrought-iron fence.  It turns out that this is an entrance to a large estate.  Next to the gate there's a plaque embedded in the fence.  A dirt road leads away to the northeast.#Northwest Corner.#You are outside the northwest corner of a wrought-iron fence which leads off to the south and east.  Inside, the fence is lined with high, thick bushes; making it impossible to see onto the estate grounds.#Top of the Cliff.#You are at the top of a cliff, overlooking a fog-bound beach to the south.  The smell of salt hangs thick in the air; and you can hear the waves crashing onto the beach below.  Through the thick fog you can make out the shape of a ship's mast.  There is a wrought-iron fence to the east and a path winds away to the north.#Eastern Fence.#You are outside a wrought-iron fence, running east-to-west.  To the west you can see a recess in the fence.  As you look eastward, you see that the fence continues into a clump of bushes.#Clump of Bushes.#You are at a clump of bushes, which turns out to be the northeast corner of the wrought-iron fence.  The fence runs off to the west, and leads into a forest to the south.#Inside of the Bushes.#You are inside the clump of bushes; with foliage so thick that you can't see outside.  On the ground, there is a wooden trap door.#Driveway by the Shack.#This is a spot just inside the wrought-iron gate.  A dirt driveway lined with huge trees, winds off to the south.  To the east is a small guard shack.#Guard Shack.#There's a strong, musty odor here.  With cobwebs hanging from the ceiling and mouse tracks running across the dusty floor, it's apparent that the house has been abandoned for some time.#Drive by the Monument.#The tree-lined drive runs north and south, with a monument on the eastern side of the road.  To the south you can make out the shape of a large building through the trees.  An intersecting drive leads off to the west.#Drive Intersection.#Here, a north-south drive intersects with a tree-lined driveway running east and west.  To the southeast there is an opening in the trees.  Through the opening you can see a stone mansion which appears very large, even at this distance.#Stable Entrance.#This is the main entrance to a large, dilapidated stable.  A tree-lined driveway leads off to the north and there are tall bushes to the east.  Beyond the bushes you can see a massive stone mansion.#Subterranean Passage.#You are in a dark subterranean passage.  Squeaky sounds and the pattering of little feet pervade the darkness around you.  A large passage runs north and south here, and a small tunnel leads down to the east.#Cemetery Entrance.#This is the entrance to a cemetery; bounded by a tall, wrought-iron fence.  As you peer through the entranceway you can see a foreboding stone building.  In a far corner of the cemetery you can make out the shape of a number of gravestones.#Cemetery.#You are inside the cemetery; somehow, it feels eerie and cold here.  To the west there is a stone mausoleum with a massive iron door.  A south-bound path leads to an area of gravestones.#Graveyard.#This section of the cemetery is very cold.  A number of the family's graves stand here; arranged in several neat rows and marked by stone tablets.  A stone monument marks the end of a winding, eastbound path.  Gazing over your surroundings, you find your eyes being drawn to a grave on the edge of the yard; covered in a thick stand of grass and marked by an ancient stone cross.#Mausoleum.#You are inside the mausoleum; a large, stately tomb permeated by cold and dampness.  A marble coffin sits against the northern wall and the southern wall is occupied by a granite coffin.  The far corner is lined with a wall made of beautiful, pure-white marble; with a large slab of granite leaning against it. An iron door opens to the east.#Stable.#You are inside a dilapidated stable.  There are several stalls for animals here; but they are empty.  There's a main entrance to the north and a side door opens to the east.#Stable Side Entrance.#This is the east side of the stable. To the south there is a cliff which provides a view of the fog-bound beach below.  A path leads eastward to a massive stone mansion; to the west, a doorway opens into the stable.#Service Entrance.#You are standing at a large, utilitarian doorway that was probably used as a service entrance.  To the south you can see the edge of a cliff which overlooks the beach below.  A path leads off to the west.#End of the Driveway.#This is the end of a tree-lined drive, leading off to the east.  A garden shed sits on the north side of the drive.#Shed.#You are inside an old, broken-down shed; which must have been used for the storage of gardening tools.#Styx River, South.#You are on the southern edge of the Styx river.  To the south, you can see the shoreline and subterranean cove.  As you gaze to the north, you see a wide expanse of river before you.  The river flows gently here, caressing and soothing you in its wake.#Dark Forest.#You are surrounded by a dense, dark forest; with thick bushes all around.  A trap door is embedded in the ground.#Front of the Mansion.#You are in front of a massive granite mansion; a monument to the accumulation of excessive wealth.  Interestingly, the granite seems to give off a mellow golden hue.  Stone steps lead up to a large ornamental entrance.  To the west, a tree-lined drive winds away and a path leads off to the east.#Mansion Entrance.#You are standing at a large ornamental entrance, decorated with beautifully detailed figures and a large, intricately carved, oak door.  However, much of the artwork is buried in cobwebs which have spun their own unique and varied shapes.#Garden.#This must have been a beautiful garden at one time; although the flower beds have long overgrown with weeds and only a few wild flowers remain.  An eastbound path leads into a dark, haunting forest.  To the west, a large set of garden doors open into the mansion.#Patio.#This is a patio on the south side of the mansion, bounded to the west by a stone wall made up of beautifully carved figures.  From here you can look down onto a beach, buried in a thick fog.  Old stone steps lead down the cliffs.#Beach.#This is a sandy section of beach.  You can't help but notice that the colour of the sand is pure white.  As you listen to waves crash on the beach, you notice the distinctive smell of the salty ocean.  Peering westward through the fog you can make out the shape of a ship's mast.  Old stone steps lead up the cliffs from here.#Western Beach.#The beach begins to turn rocky here; in fact, the rocks make it impossible to go further.  Through the fog you can see cliffs to the north; they seem quite tall.  There is a ship run aground here; a speedy-looking cutter, which could have been used by smugglers to transport their booty across the channel.#Eastern Beach.#This is a rocky section of beach; which turns to sand as you follow the beach to the west.  To the east the terrain appears to be more and more rugged; and the north is blocked by tall cliffs, with large rocks protruding from the cliff's base.  The fog is quite soupy here, making it difficult to see; but the salty air provides a freshness you won't soon forget.#Rocks.#You are on top of the rocks at the base of the cliffs.  Somehow, the air feels quite calm here; maybe because you're so close to the cliffs.  A crevice provides an entrance into the cliffs here.#Subterranean Entrance.#This is a damp underground cavern.  You can see light coming from a crevice above you; a passage leads off to the north.#Subterranean Passage.#You are in a dark passage; as near as you can tell the passage leads off to the east.  To the west, you can see an opening in a granite wall.#Dark Forest.#You are surrounded by a dense, dark forest; with thick bushes all around.#Dark Forest.#Yo