s though it could have been used as a hideout.  On the east wall some granite blocks have been removed, revealing a dark opening beyond.  A stairway leads up from here and a passage leads off to the south.#Torture Chamber.#You are in an old torture chamber.  From the looks of the rack and other obscene implements, it appears that the torturers had quite a time; much of the equipment is caked with layers of dried blood and rotten flesh.  In the far corner you see a dark opening, cloaked in layers of dust and cobwebs.  An iron maiden occupies the western wall of the chamber.#Dungeon.#You are in a dark, damp dungeon; surrounded by walls made of stone.  A small, armoured door opens to the north.#Foyer.#You are in a large foyer with a high, ornamental ceiling.  A stairway lined with a handrail of beautifully carved figures, descends from a second floor balcony.  Above a stately fireplace there is a tabard, blazoned with the family's coat of arms.  Doorways lead off in all directions.#Drawing Room.#Finely sculptured woodwork adorns the walls of this richly furnished room.   A mahogany side table sits next to a finely carved sofa; and a fireplace is embedded in the western wall.  Arched doorways lead off to the west and south.#Conservatory.#Richly carved moulding and paneling surrounds a fireplace on the north wall of this room.  The remaining walls are lined with bookcases containing beautifully-bound novels.  A spinet sits in one corner of the room while a sofa and side table sit in the centre.#Secret Landing.#This is a dark stairway landing, with steps leading both up and down.  On the north wall there is a wooden panel with a lever beside it.#Eastern Great Hall.#This is the eastern part of the great hall.  The splendor of the carved wooden cornice and decorated ceiling, combined with the doric pilasters bordering each of the entrance doorways, create an atmosphere of rich elegance.  A spinet is here, surrounded by sofa and chairs; and a fireplace occupies the north wall. Doors open into a garden to the east.#Dark Tunnel.#You are in a dark tunnel.  Interestingly, it feels rather warm here; like the air is being heated from below.  A faint rumbling sound intrudes on the silence; and as you touch the rock wall, you can feel a slight vibration.  A wide passage leads up to the west and a steep, narrow tunnel descends to the south.#Western Great Hall.#You are in the western part of the great hall.  A spiral staircase, adorned with intricate carvings, descends from an upstairs balcony.  The doric pilasters are particularly prominent here, blending with the carved cornice to create a magnificent chamber.  The silk and paintings which line the walls complete the feeling of elegance.#Secret Landing.#This is a dark stairway landing, with a narrow stairway leading up.  You can see a wooden panel on the south wall.  Next to the panel there is a lever.#Billiard Room.#An intricately carved billiard table dominates this chamber.  The north wall boasts a stately fireplace, bordered with rich mahogany paneling and moulding; comfortable furnishings complete a feeling of subdued elegance.#Breakfast Parlour.#You are in the breakfast parlour; a tastefully furnished room.  In the centre of the room is a breakfast table and chairs.  A decorated ceiling blends splendidly with the overmantel, above the fireplace.#Styx River, Central.#You are in the centre of the Styx river.  The cavern ceiling is very high here, making is seem almost like a cloudy day.  To the south, you can make out the subterranean cove in the distance.  Northward, a wide expanse of river runs past the shoreline of a cavern; the high ceiling making it seem distant and insignificant.  The flowing river washes by, licking at the dinghy.#Kitchen.#You are in the kitchen; where the cook slaved over the kitchen table, making various dishes to delight the palate.  A fireplace occupies the eastern wall, with a large black kettle hanging above it.  Doorways lead to the north and west; a utility door opens to the south.#Still Room.#This is the room where spice and medicine preparation took place.  Against the north wall there is a table with a large cupboard beside it.#Inferno.#You are in a centre of a raging inferno; with intense, swirling heat all around you.  The rumbling is dominant here, masking all other sounds.  A large marble altar is standing here, oblivious to the heat and flames that lick at its surface.#Subterranean Cliffs.#This is the end of a steep tunnel.  To the east, the tunnel opens out to a subterranean cliff, overlooking a massive cavern.  Looking out over the cliffs you can see the source of the rumbling; a blazing inferno covering the eastern side of the cavern.  Even at this distance, the hot air sweeps across your face; baking your flesh.#Dining Room.#This is the formal dining room; a chamber of prominent grandeur.  The large mahogany table and chairs dominate a room appointed with detailed crown moulding, elegant walnut wainscotting, and a stately fireplace.#Guest Parlour.#You are in the guest parlour, a richly appointed chamber with exquisite furnishings.  The sofa and chairs are upholstered in fine fabric and surround a fireplace of stately appeal; the overmantel blending beautifully with a decorated ceiling and crown moulding.#End of the West Hall.#This is the end of a hallway which leads off to the west.  As you look along the hall, you can't help but notice the elegant silk and paintings that adorn the walls.  From here, doorways open to the north, south, and east.#Hall at the Foyer.#You are in an east-west hallway, with walls decorated in silk and paintings. To the north, a doorway opens into a foyer of stately elegance.#Hall at the Parlour.#You are in a silk-lined hallway, where a south-bound hall intersects with an east-bound hallway.  A doorway opens to the north.#Hall at Dining Room.#You are in a north-south hallway, lined with paintings and red silk.  Doors open to the east and west.#Hall at the Kitchen.#You are in a hallway, where a north-bound hall intersects an east-bound hall. A doorway opens to the south and stairs lead both up and down.#Hall at Breakfast Room#This is an east-west hallway; with walls decorated in silk and paintings.  From here, doorways open to the north and south.#SE Hall Intersection.#You are at a hallway intersection, where a south-bound hall meets a west-bound hall.  Doorways open to the north and east.#Patio Entrance.#You are in a wide, tastefully decorated hallway.  To the north you can see an intersecting hallway, leading off to the west.  A doorway leads to the south.#Guest Bedroom.#You are in a large, tastefully decorated bedroom containing a comfortable, four-poster bed.  A fireplace, surrounded with beautifully-carved moulding and paneling, enhances an already restful atmosphere.#Secret Landing.#This is a dark stairway landing, with narrow stairs leading down. There is a wooden panel on the north wall; and a lever next to the panel.#Sitting Room.#This is the lady's sitting room.  The room is in shambles, with furnishings torn from the walls and strewn about.  It looks like someone ransacked the room, perhaps looking for something valuable.#Secret Landing.#This is a dark stairway landing, with narrow stairs leading up and down. On the south wall you see a wooden panel; next to the panel is a lever.#Lady's Bedroom.#You are in the Lady's bedroom; a richly appointed room with a large, elegant four-poster bed.  A fireplace, embedded in a wall of mahogany paneling, provides a finishing touch to the subdued, peaceful chamber.  Doors lead to the north, northwest, and west.#Parlour.#This is a comfortably decorated parlour; set aside for quiet moments between the Lady and Master.  Elegantly upholstered furniture create a feeling of peaceful relaxation.#Inferno's Edge.#You are near the blazing inferno; a massive fire covering the eastern side of the cavern.  The heat is intense here, baking your flesh in its swirling gusts of wind.  From behind the inferno you 