ack stairwell.  Stairs lead both up and down from here, and a hallway leads off to the east.  The stairs leading up have been blocked by a large pile of debris, apparently the result of some battered upstairs walls.#Hall at West Gallery.#You are in a north-south hallway, with walls decorated in silk and paintings. Doors open to the east and west.#NW Hall Intersection.#This is the northwest corner of a tastefully decorated hallway; where an east-bound hall intersects a south-bound hall.  A doorway leads to the north.#Cavern.#You are in the centre of a massive cavern; where the walls are emitting a soft glow to light your way.  Distant rumbling sounds intrude on the silence; the rumbling seems to coincide with the vibrations in the stone floor.  The cavern is quite warm; almost too warm.  Scanning the cavern, you see the Styx river, running from the northwest to southeast.  Gazing off to the north you can see a distant fire, raging out of control.#Fore deck.#This is the fore deck of the cutter.  A main mast protrudes from the deck and the sails are rolled around the boom.  To the south, you can follow the deck to the ship's aft.#Styx River, North.#You are near the northern edge of the Styx river; a high, expansive ceiling looming above you.  Even on the river, you can hear (or feel) a rumbling in the distance; seeming to make the river water vibrate with tiny waves.#Subterranean Cove.#You are in a subterranean cove, on the edge of a massive cavern.  A soft glow shines off the walls, making artificial light unnecessary here.  Interestingly, the walls seem to emit deep vibrations which coincide with a distant rumbling sound.  To the north, you see a wide river flowing by; running from the northwest to southeast.  Across the river, you can make out the shape of the northern shoreline; the cavern continuing further than the eye can see.  An old shroud hangs conspicuously on the stone wall, creating a lifelike silhouette.#Attic.#This is a dark attic, buried in dust and cobwebs.  In the far corner you can make out the shape of an old chest.  A broken-down doorway leads out to the west but the doorway is blocked by a large pile of debris, making passage impossible.  A stairway leads down into darkness.#Aft Deck.#You are on the aft deck of the cutter; with the position behind the ship's steering wheel providing a clear, unobstructed view beyond the ship's bow. Next to a rear-mounted canon there is a powder locker, firmly attached to the deck. An opening in the deck leads down to a cargo hold, and a doorway provides an entrance into the ship's cabin.#Ship's Cabin.#You are in the cabin of the ship, a small compartment furnished with cots and a built-in cupboard.  In such cramped quarters it's clear that this was only used for sleeping and shelter.  A doorway leads out to the south.#floorboard#Near the center of the room, a floorboard sits beside a hole in the floor.#There's a deep covering of dust on the floor; but near the center, you can see what appears to be the lip of a slightly raised floorboard.#There's a deep covering of dust on the floor; but near the center of the room, you see a hole in the floor with a floorboard sitting next to it.#gold key#It's a gold key with intricate carvings.#hole#grimy skeleton#    A grimy skeleton, laying face down in the dirt.#The skeleton has a very sad look on his face; he must be unhappy.#Strangely, the skeleton seems to have a smile on his boney face.#stone cross#The stone cross looks like it has some writing on it.#The stone cross says:@ @        Bless our dear brother William@             May he rot in HELL@#slab of granite#The slab of granite is large and heavy.#The slab has been pushed aside, revealing an opening in the western wall.#hole#A hole is embedded in the ground, leading into a shadowy darkness.#marble coffin#The coffin is made of marble which has a subtle yellow tone.  There seems to be an inscription on the side of the coffin.#    Lord John Leominster III@           1635 - 1699#plaque#@      Please Wait @          for @   Service Attendant@#wrought-iron fence#The fence is tall, and made of wrought-iron.#white cliffs#The cliffs are quite steep here; they look like they're made of white chalk.#bushes#medieval monument#The monument is a statue of a medieval warrior, wearing a tunic over armour; the statue is holding a sword and shield.#mausoleum#The mausoleum is a large, stately tomb; constructed of granite stone. Strangely, the granite has assumed a mellow golden hue.#stone monument#The monument is made of stone; it looks like is has some writing on it.#The inscription reads:@ @    Leominster Family Cemetery@      May All Rest In Peace@#body of Lord John#    The body of Lord John Leominster.#Lord John appears to be resting quietly.#black skull#    A large black skull.#The skull is charred and blackened, almost like it was set afire.#family graves#The family graves sit peacefully, all in a row.#The inscriptions are too faint to read.#grassy grave#The grave is covered by a thick stand of grass and seems to have finger holes on either side of the plot.#Apparently someone has started to dig-up Uncle Henri's grave; there's a pile of dirt next to it.#The grave of Uncle Henri has been dug-up; there's a large pile of dirt sitting next to it.#crimson silk#The silk is a rich crimson; it probably came from the far east.#quantity of vampire's blood#    A pool of vampire's blood.#The blood is a rich crimson colour; the donator was extremely well-fed.#body of Uncle Henri#    The body of Uncle Henri, resting peacefully.#Strangely, his rose coloured cheeks and full red lips give the feeling that he's alive and well fed.#Uncle Henri's eyes are wide open and he has an anguished look on his face. He must have died a horrible death.#Uncle Henri's penetrating gaze is hypnotizing.  It looks like he's going to eat you!#marble altar#The altar is tall, with a large flat surface.#stone monument#On the edge of the forest stands a stone monument, inscribed with ancient, bl