every.   @   The nobleman therefore challenges @all men, brave or coward, to find the @treasure; thwarting the deadly will of @the crazed, vindictive spirits of @Elysium Downs....#Diary#Dear diary;           March 15, 1724 @@It looks as though Charles was correct @in his surmise that the spirit is, in @fact the ghost of William. I knew that @William did not think well of us;  @especially after Charles turned him @over to the police.  But to return as @a spirit must require intense hate. @I'm afraid the convultions that @brought about the death of Charles @could only have come from the world @of spirits. @    I've locked many of the rooms @with hammer and nail, for the ghost @has been rampant in them.  Most of the @servants have deserted the house; I'm @afraid they fear the death of convul- @sions that killed poor Charles.  It's @scarey, but I don't know what to do.#fortune hunter#You are an eighteenth century fortune hunter, responding to Lord Barnwell's challenge to seek the Leominster treasure.#pair of hands#fireplace#It's a large, stately fireplace.#wolfdog#Laying in the corner is a wolfdog, apparently dead.#The wolfdog is lying open, with its guts hanging out.#heart#The heart is hanging out with the other guts, but it seems to be beating.#As you examine the heart, you notice that it's beating.#travel bag#Sitting on the ground beside you is your trusty traveling bag.#mangled corpse#Face-down in the middle of the floor is a mangled corpse.#The body is only partly decomposed, but the man sustained a brutal beating.#headless corpse#Slumped over in the far corner is a bloody, headless corpse.#The corpse is a headless hulk; giving off a sickening odor.#ugly corpse#Face-up on the floor is the body of a terror-stricken man; an ugly grimace painted across his face.#The man was stricken with terror; he probably died of fright.#cavern of jewels#    A dimly-lit cavern, with many-coloured jewels embedded in the walls.#From your limited range of view, it appears that thousands of precious jewels are embedded in the cavern walls.  There's easily enough wealth to please the most greedy of royalty.#granite cliff#